text: Kotryna Teterevkova (born 23 January 2002) is a Lithuanian swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre breaststroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Lithuanian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Female breaststroke swimmers
